title: For Sale:  Stevens 410 Side x Side
postcontent: This J. Stevens .410 side x side is dated 1915 to 1919 based on patent info engraved on the right side of the shotgun and the manufacturers code engraved on the left under side of the barrel. The shotgun was made using the features of the G. S. Lewis patent 1,136,247 issued April 20, 1915 which covered the use of coil spring driven strikers in hammerless double barrel guns rather than traditional revolving internal hammers. This design was the mainstay of double barrel guns for Stevens and trade brand models from 1915 to 1942.the numbers on the left under side of the barrel. The number 97 on the barrel means this model was manufactured between 1912 to 1919 with approx. 16,000 guns being made with this code.The full code on the left under side of the barrel is H181  97. Savage/Stevens started a letter code for the Stevens models in 1949 with H being 1956. The letters were mainly in a circle or oval with a number located somewhere on the gun. This one isn't like that!I've left the patinia on it since I'm not sure if cleaning it or restoring the finish will affect it's value.3" chamber26" barrelCase is included if you want it.A flying duck and grass reeds are engraved in the metal on the left side as well to the right of STEVENSIt's in Great condition!Make an offer!Prefer Paypal for payment.email me for more photos.also sellingArmalite AR 10ACOG ScopeBenelli 12ga left hand
